Quick guide for ProcuderPal v 1.3.6 (beta) installation

1 - Download the max for live device folder and place it inside your ableton library and add it to a MIDI track in Ableton Live

2 - Download the Claude Desktop Extension inside the claude-extension-repo

3 - Install the Extension in Claude Desktop
Go to Claude Desktop → Settings → Extensions and
If you already have extensions installed, drag and drop Producer_Pal.mcpb into the Extensions screen  Or,
if you have never installed a Claude Desktop extension before, you need to click "Advanced settings" on the Extensions screen,
then click "Install extension...", and choose the Producer_Pal.mcpb file.

4 - Complete the Installation
Don't forget to click "Install" and complete the Claude Desktop installation

5 - Verify Installation
You should see Producer Pal tools in Claude's "Connectors" menu (make sure it's enabled when starting a conversation)

6 - 6. Start Using Producer Pal
Start a conversation with "connect to ableton"
Allow Producer Pal tools to be used when Claude tries to use them




